# README.md Guidelines

## Structure
- Project title and brief description
- Screenshots of key screens (updated as features complete)
- Features list (synchronized with specifications.md)
- Installation instructions
- Usage guide
- Technology stack
- Testing information
- Contributors section

## Updates
- README should be updated after each feature completion
- Features section should mirror specifications.md (complete/incomplete)
- Installation instructions must be verified with each update
- Screenshots should be replaced with updated versions
- Update technology stack as new libraries are added

## GitHub Format
- Use GitHub-flavored markdown
- Include badges for build status and version
- Use relative links for navigation
- Include collapsible sections for detailed information
- Format code examples with proper syntax highlighting
